What a perfect reading spot
Perched high above the ground. 
A peaceful place like this at home
Is very rarely found.
Apart from the odd squirrel
Or perhaps a bounding deer,
But nothing like my sisters, 
Not as noisy, no way near. 
My goodness, it’s so comfy, 
Nice and firm, yet spongy light.
And when I’m feeling peckish,
I just take a little bite!

So into December 
And full steam ahead. 
With all hands on deck 
We’re a full team said Ted.
There’s presents to buy 
And there’s greetings to write. 
With a break in between 
We’ll have time for a bite. 
So pop in the mince pies 
Set the oven mark four 
And make sure you’re generous 
With cream when you pour!

#advent  #saturday  #festive  #christmas  #vintage #recycle  #dollytreasures  #toys #dolls

On a chilly Monday morning,
We carried home our tree.
Well, now I come to think of it
The carrier was me.
Ted said, he couldn’t reach the trunk 
For all the prickly branches.
The doggies thought, 
They’d just play dumb…
The lazy little chancers.
And so I struggled with good cheer
Just like a Christmas elf.
For if you want a job well done,
You’d best do it yourself!

#christmastree  #suffolk #monday #pets #dollytreasures  #dollphotography  #countryside  #poetry  #whimsical

I brought my toadstool home with me
What else was I to do?
If you were in my shoes I’m sure
You would have done so too. 
And what a lovely house it makes 
With such a pretty roof.
It gives me perfect shelter
Whilst I sit and look aloof.
And underneath my books and things
I very safely keep,
A mattress with a patchwork quilt 
Where I can safely sleep!

A good deportments’s
Most important 
That’s what we’ve been told.
So how long  with these books
Upon her head can Delphine hold?
Of course, she’s been selective 
Over which books she has chosen 
Though little does the content matter 
When you’re standing frozen.
Dickens, Scott Fitzgerald can not 
Help one in this matter. 
For any moment soon I think 
Will end in much a clatter!

We’ve hung our stockings early 
With the strikes and this and that.
Don’t want our Christmas landing
Like a pancake, flip-flop-flat.
Santa and his elves need all 
The help to spread the cheer 
That’s why we’re trying extra hard
To be most good this year.
We know that things are tough
And so we don’t ask for a lot.
As long as we’ve each other 
Then the things we need
We’ve got!

Ted always makes me anxious
Around this time of year.
I find myself on high alert,
To try and keep him near.
And trying’s not an easy task 
Believe me when I say.
That bear he likes to wonder off 
Habitually stray.
I think I’ll get a tracker, 
A James Bond microchip.
Insert it with a special gun
He’ll only feel a nip!

As Christmas Eve draws near. 
Grownups get nostalgic 
As they look back on the year.
And here inside the Mischief house
There’s merry in the making,
Festive scenes of winter dreams

I’m sure you’ve heard it said.
So this year’s very special 
For Mermaid and her Ted.
They have their baby Stickleback 
Their family’s now complete.
Someone cute to cuddle ,
With tiny hands and feet.

Like all good girls and boys,

It’s always a real delight, to do the @benjamin_pollocks_toyshop window. 
For the latest display, I have chosen the Theme of Alice in Wonderland. 
The process is rather like creating a collage. I begin by putting the wreath together. This is a bit like a mood board and gives me a foundation to build around. Once that’s done I can get on with the main characters, Alice and the White Rabbit. It took me a few attempts to get Alice’s hair right , the first hair I used was too dark, I then tried a yellow wool, before I found the perfect thing hidden away in a drawer……if only I’d found that in the first place! Her her clothes are made from old shirts, I don’t like anything to look too new, so the worn cotton works perfectly. My mother very kindly dropped everything she was doing to make White Rabbit at very short notice. so I’d have enough time to dress him. His waistcoat is made from a pair of trousers I found in the charity shop as they were the exact yellow, his jacket is from a beautiful red wool cloth that I found years ago and his cravat is an old tie. Oh…..and his pocket handkerchief is a piece cut from a vintage Prada bikini! 
It’s then just a matter of bringing it all together with the toys from the shop, and so satisfying when it’s all done! 
I do hope if you’re out and about in London’s Covent Garden you will get an opportunity to visit the window! ✨😘✨✨✨

Pull tight on string like reigns.
Different colours, follow others

Pink or red, or blue instead?

We’re so not getting up today,
It’s far too cold outside. 
And so we’ll stay here snuggled up 
Where all day we’ll abide.
We’ll ring downstairs for tea at times
And sip it at our leisure.
It’s funny how such simple things 
Can bring one so much pleasure.
So plump those feather pillows up
All creatures big and small.
We highly recommend it, 
It’s Sunday after all!

All alone in the woods my dear
So far away from home?
Would you like some company,
A handsome chaperone?
It really isn’t safe my dear,
To travel by oneself. 
For predators lurk in the shadows 
Creeping round with stealth. 
Let me take the liberty,
Permit me if you would?
To walk beside you cheek by jowl.
I really think you should!

Grandma what big eyes you have,
They weren’t like that before. 
And what has happened to your hands
I think I see a claw?
Those teeth of yours 
Look mighty sharp,
In fact I think they’re real.
They don’t look like the plastic ones
That help you chew your meal. 
Your voice, it doesn’t sound the same 
It’s very deep and husky. 
And you don’t smell like lavender,
You smell all foul and musky.
Perhaps you have a headache,
For you’re not yourself today?
My goodness me! 
Is that the time?
I’d best be on my way!

And wash up all the dishes.

Saturday is shopping day,
For groceries and such.
And so we’re dressed and ready 
‘Cause we love to shop so much.
We  wiz round the supermarket 
Hanging on the trolly,
We grab things off the shelves 
We’re not allowed, it’s fun by golly!

In the healthy breakfast section,

And things filled with confection.

And cans of cherry pop,
We through them in the trolley 
With a very happy plop.
We know it’s very naughty 
But it gives us such a thrill.
To hide it with the boring stuff
And get it through the till!

I would like to give special thanks and credit to my mother,  who, at my  request, made this amazing Mrs Witch for me.
As a child, my grandmother would fuel my imagination with  tales of Mrs Witch. I would love it when I went to stay with her and she would let me pull out all her old dresses and hats. She had a red taffeta gown that I absolutely adored which I would put on and swan around the garden pretending to be Snow White!
She often recalled the time when I came running over to her whilst out playing, saying ‘“ Grandma, there are princesses in the forest aren’t there?” My fellow child companions were perhaps  not quite as willing to believe in such fanciful things as me!
Although my grandmother is no longer with us she is still very much here in spirit through all that she has passed down and my mother and I would like to dedicate today’s story in her memory. ❤️

So me I would not ever.

They have no fear at all,
So high they have a birds-eye view
Beyond the garden wall.

You make me feel quite faint.
